11:10.737 --> 11:13.638
Howard Cosell,
give me the sweet stuff.
(REMOTE CONTROL CLICKS)

11:13.640 --> 11:16.207
BEVERLY: Murray,
turn that TV off!

11:16.209 --> 11:17.275
<i>Or not.</i>

11:17.277 --> 11:17.976
Oh, God.

11:17.978 --> 11:21.846
Barry hasn't called.
He's been gone almost an hour.

11:21.848 --> 11:24.683
I called
Roger McFadden's house.

11:24.850 --> 11:25.517
No one's answering.

11:25.519 --> 11:27.152
How many times
have you called?
Eight.

11:27.154 --> 11:28.553
When you hit 15,
then we'll talk.

11:28.555 --> 11:31.556
(GAME PLAYING ON TV)
So you're just gonna sit here
and watch a baseball game

11:31.558 --> 11:35.393
when our son might be
laying facedown
in a ditch somewhere.

11:35.395 --> 11:38.830
Might be.
But might not be.

11:38.832 --> 11:41.032
The only thing
we know for sure is

11:41.034 --> 11:42.834
I'm watching
the world series.

11:42.836 --> 11:44.035
How do you sleep at night?

11:44.037 --> 11:48.406
Not as good as I do
during the day, but not bad.

11:49.075 --> 11:51.743
Relax. Kid's gonna be fine.

11:51.745 --> 11:52.944
<i>But he wasn't.</i>

11:52.946 --> 11:55.714
It's okay.
I can fix this.

11:56.415 --> 11:57.215
Oh!

11:57.217 --> 11:59.451
(PANTING) Oh! Oh!

11:59.453 --> 12:01.286
Okay. All right.

12:01.288 --> 12:02.854
(CONTINUES PANTING)

12:02.856 --> 12:04.689
(COINS DROP)

12:06.625 --> 12:08.526
No!

12:08.528 --> 12:09.794
Mom!

12:09.796 --> 12:13.131
(SOBBING)
I'm at Roger's house!

12:13.432 --> 12:15.266
I got here safely!

12:15.268 --> 12:17.435
(COINS DROPPING)
I love...

12:17.437 --> 12:19.003
<i>While Barry's night was</i>
<i>off and running,</i>

12:19.005 --> 12:22.607
<i>my grandfather's was</i>
<i>just winding down.</i>

12:22.609 --> 12:25.643
Yeah, I'd love for you
to stay the night, but, uh...

12:25.645 --> 12:29.114
(LAUGHS)
Turns out I got a meeting
first thing in the morning.

12:29.116 --> 12:31.049
Well, I thought you
retired ten years ago.

12:31.051 --> 12:35.153
Yeah, well, I still do
part-time consulting
and the occasional...

12:35.155 --> 12:37.322
Do you need money
for a cab?

12:37.324 --> 12:38.790
What's this?

12:38.792 --> 12:39.257
Oh.

12:39.259 --> 12:41.292
This is one of those things
from the commercial.

12:41.294 --> 12:42.460
Well, you don't wear
one of these?

12:42.462 --> 12:46.097
No, no. This is just,
uh, it's a gag gift

12:46.099 --> 12:50.268
from some of the guys down
at the boxing club, and...

12:50.336 --> 12:51.770
Hilarious.

12:51.772 --> 12:55.774
Well, this has been fun.
I'll call you.

12:56.375 --> 12:57.108
Uh... No.

12:57.110 --> 13:01.446
I'll call you.
I, I do the calling.

13:02.948 --> 13:05.283
Unbelievable.

13:09.021 --> 13:10.655
(CRACK)
Oh!

13:10.723 --> 13:11.523
(THUD)

13:11.525 --> 13:12.423
Son of a bitch!

13:12.425 --> 13:13.858
BEVERLY: Yes, I'm calling
to see if my son

13:13.860 --> 13:17.362
might have been brought
into your emergency room
earlier tonight.

13:17.364 --> 13:23.001
Uh, he is 5'8",
dark hair, fair skin,
beautiful brown eyes.

13:23.003 --> 13:26.571
(VOICE BREAKS) Oh, he was just
the sweetest little baby
you've ever seen.

13:26.573 --> 13:31.242
(NORMAL VOICE) What? No?
Okay, thank you.

13:31.410 --> 13:32.677
(BASEBALL GAME
PLAYING ON TV)
Oh!

13:32.679 --> 13:35.747
What is that pitch?
That's garbage!

13:35.749 --> 13:36.581
I hate you, Dickie Noles!

13:36.583 --> 13:40.785
Okay. He's not
in the emergency room
or the police station

13:40.787 --> 13:42.854
or the roller rink
or the batting cages

13:42.856 --> 13:45.957
or any of the four
ice cream shops
in the green zone,

13:45.959 --> 13:48.092
and I have failed
as a mother.

13:48.094 --> 13:50.395
You're good
at other things.

13:50.496 --> 13:52.397
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

13:53.465 --> 13:55.400
(RINGING)

13:55.968 --> 13:56.701
Barry!

13:56.703 --> 13:58.570
No, it's, it's just me,
darling.

13:58.572 --> 14:02.240
Your line's been busy for
quite a while now, and I...

14:02.242 --> 14:03.708
Can't talk now!

14:03.710 --> 14:04.742
Damn it!

14:04.744 --> 14:06.644
(DIAL TONE)

14:10.316 --> 14:11.416
I can't take it anymore.

14:11.418 --> 14:13.117
Go out and find
our baby, Murray.

14:13.119 --> 14:16.154
Please! If I go out, I'll find
out what happened in the game!

14:16.156 --> 14:19.691
Enough with the baseball.
What is wrong with you?

14:19.693 --> 14:21.893
Why aren't you worried?
He's out there.

14:21.895 --> 14:24.028
He could be injured
or cold or hungry.

14:24.030 --> 14:28.199
What if he has to make?
He doesn't use
public bathrooms!

14:28.201 --> 14:30.702
Bevy, calm down, okay?

14:30.704 --> 14:32.103
Every time our kids
leave the house,

14:32.105 --> 14:35.874
you assume that they're dead
until they prove otherwise.

14:35.876 --> 14:39.777
Know that they're smart,
responsible kids.

14:39.779 --> 14:41.613
Assume that they're alive.

14:41.615 --> 14:44.148
That's the stupidest thing
you've ever said!

14:44.150 --> 14:45.817
I'll see you in a bit.

14:45.819 --> 14:48.052
(TELEPHONE RINGS)
(GASPS)

14:48.654 --> 14:49.387
(RINGING)
Barry?

14:49.389 --> 14:53.658
No, it's not Barry. It's me.
Put Adam on the phone.

14:53.660 --> 14:56.394
Adam, get in here,
talk to your grandfather

14:56.396 --> 14:58.763
so he'll stop
tying up the line!

14:59.131 --> 15:01.165
Make it quick.

15:01.300 --> 15:01.833
Yeah, Pops?

15:01.835 --> 15:03.468
ADULT ADAM:
<i>While Pops was looking</i>
<i>for a little help,</i>

15:03.470 --> 15:05.336
<i>my dad was out</i>
<i>looking for Barry,</i>

15:05.338 --> 15:07.105
<i>and he was growing</i>
<i>increasingly worried</i>

15:07.107 --> 15:10.275
<i>that he'd find out</i>
<i>what happened in the game.</i>

15:10.277 --> 15:10.875
(CLICKS)

15:10.877 --> 15:12.410
MAN: (ON RADIO)
<i>Quite an emotional night</i>
<i>for Phillies fans...</i>

15:12.412 --> 15:15.113
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

15:15.115 --> 15:15.813
(TURNS RADIO OFF)

15:15.815 --> 15:21.252
ADULT ADAM:  <i>If my dad</i>
<i>didn't find Barry soon,</i>
<i>my brother was gonna pay.</i>

15:21.254 --> 15:21.986
Excuse me, Officer.

15:21.988 --> 15:25.156
Did you see a high school
kid driving around here?

15:25.158 --> 15:26.057
Curly hair, kind of lumpy?

15:26.059 --> 15:30.361
No, but there's a party
in the woods down
by Alverthorpe Park.

15:30.363 --> 15:30.795
Okay.

15:30.797 --> 15:32.530
Hey, Phillies!
Man, how about...

15:32.532 --> 15:35.166
(HORN BLARING)
No, no, no!

15:35.601 --> 15:37.602
I just wanna watch
the world series!

15:37.604 --> 15:39.637
I'm gonna kill
that kid!

15:42.141 --> 15:43.708
Pops? Pops!

15:43.710 --> 15:45.343
Over here!

15:46.045 --> 15:47.812
What happened?

15:47.814 --> 15:50.014
I have fallen...

15:50.149 --> 15:53.584
And I cannot get up.

15:55.721 --> 15:56.854
There you go.

15:56.856 --> 15:59.424
Easy. Little more.

15:59.426 --> 16:01.225
Whoa! Pull your robe down.

16:01.227 --> 16:02.193
It's a Kimono.

16:02.195 --> 16:03.494
Pull your Kimono down.

16:03.496 --> 16:05.730
It's designed to be showy.

16:05.732 --> 16:06.864
Well, it's working.

16:06.866 --> 16:08.066
Just don't look down!

16:08.068 --> 16:10.868
What did I just see?
It was like a robin's nest!

16:10.870 --> 16:12.837
It's an unflattering angle.

16:12.839 --> 16:13.838
What's going on down there?

16:13.840 --> 16:17.909
Stop looking down and get
me to the couch already!

16:17.911 --> 16:19.911
Oh!
Oh! Okay.

16:20.012 --> 16:20.445
You good?

16:20.447 --> 16:22.747
Yeah, okay.
I'm, I'm good now.

16:22.749 --> 16:25.416
Thanks for dropping by, kid.

16:26.418 --> 16:27.819
Are you sure you're good?

16:27.821 --> 16:31.189
Of course. Like you
even need to ask.

16:31.191 --> 16:33.191
It's just that you said
that you never fell before.

16:33.193 --> 16:37.395
I threw my back out.
It could happen to anyone.

16:40.132 --> 16:41.899
(CLATTERING)

16:42.001 --> 16:44.402
So what do you
wanna do with this?

16:44.404 --> 16:46.004
Chuck it!

16:47.706 --> 16:51.376
I get it. This thing might
be embarrassing, but...

16:51.378 --> 16:54.412
No more embarrassing
than that robe.

16:54.913 --> 16:55.980
<i>For the second</i>
<i>time that night,</i>

16:55.982 --> 16:59.117
<i>I saw a part of my grandfather</i>
<i>I'd never seen before...</i>

16:59.119 --> 17:02.653
<i>The part that was</i>
<i>actually vulnerable.</i>

17:05.157 --> 17:07.392
Stop! Stop! Please!

17:07.394 --> 17:10.561
(HORN HONKING)
Stop! Sto... Uhh!

17:11.697 --> 17:13.064
Stop! Stop!

17:13.066 --> 17:16.100
(HORN HONKING)
I need your CB Radio
to call my mom...

17:16.102 --> 17:16.968
...so she knows I'm safe!

17:16.970 --> 17:19.137
(HORN BLARING)
No, no, no, no!

17:19.139 --> 17:20.505
(SCREAMING)

17:20.507 --> 17:22.673
(HORN CONTINUES BLARING)

17:25.978 --> 17:29.714
<i>My dad had spent the last hour</i>
<i>driving all over town.</i>

17:29.716 --> 17:30.648
<i>Just as he was starting</i>
<i>to think</i>

17:30.650 --> 17:34.152
<i>my mom's craziness</i>
<i>may not have been so crazy,</i>

17:34.154 --> 17:37.555
<i>he spotted</i>
<i>a familiar jacket...</i>

17:40.692 --> 17:43.127
Oh. Hi.

17:43.129 --> 17:46.064
<i>And a familiar jackass.</i>

17:47.132 --> 17:49.133
You couldn't have been
sitting up in a ditch?

17:49.135 --> 17:51.669
Or reclining comfortably
in a ditch?

17:51.671 --> 17:55.540
No, you had to be facedown,
exactly like she said!

17:55.542 --> 17:58.743
And to think I told your mom
you could be trusted,

17:58.745 --> 18:00.945
mostly 'cause I wanted
to watch the game.

18:00.947 --> 18:03.114
But you know what?
A small part of me

18:03.116 --> 18:07.885
actually thought, "Hey,
he's not a complete moron."

18:07.887 --> 18:11.756
Only some of this happened
'cause I'm a complete moron.

18:11.758 --> 18:13.724
The rest is 'cause
of mom's stupid rules.

18:13.726 --> 18:16.160
Hey, her rules are
there to protect you.

18:16.162 --> 18:19.997
I almost died when I saw
your jacket in the road.

18:21.700 --> 18:22.834
You worry about me, too?

18:22.836 --> 18:25.736
Oh, don't put words
in my mouth.

18:25.838 --> 18:27.772
Of course I do.

18:28.240 --> 18:30.875
Your mom can't know
anything about this.

18:30.877 --> 18:31.876
What? You're gonna lie to mom?

18:31.878 --> 18:34.979
Absolutely!
She finds out about this,

18:34.981 --> 18:36.080
you're not gonna be allowed
to leave the house

18:36.082 --> 18:39.383
until you're 40, and then
my life is ruined, too!

18:39.385 --> 18:40.518
Nice!
I'm off the hook, then.

18:40.520 --> 18:43.554
You are so grounded.
Secretly, though.

18:43.556 --> 18:45.756
You will choose to
stay in every weekend

18:45.758 --> 18:48.993
for the next three months,
and for the love of god,

18:48.995 --> 18:51.529
when I do let you
back out in the world,

18:51.531 --> 18:55.633
you will call me
when you get there.

18:55.635 --> 18:57.635
I will. I promise.

18:57.637 --> 18:59.504
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

19:00.606 --> 19:02.273
(HORN HONKS)

19:03.709 --> 19:05.843
(GIRL SCREAMS IN DISTANCE)

19:05.845 --> 19:07.879
I was throwing that
for a friend.

19:07.881 --> 19:11.616
And tell your stupid
sister that she's secretly
grounded, too.

19:11.618 --> 19:13.017
Thanks for being
so cool about this.

19:13.019 --> 19:17.021
I thought you'd be
in the worst mood
after the Phillies lost.

19:23.262 --> 19:24.862
Get out.

19:25.464 --> 19:27.398
Lie down.

19:27.599 --> 19:29.800
I'm gonna run you over.

19:30.235 --> 19:31.102
<i>(IT'S TRICKY</i> RESUMES PLAYING)

19:31.104 --> 19:32.537
<i>♪ It's tricky to rock around,</i>
<i>to rock around... ♪</i>

19:32.539 --> 19:35.173
ADULT ADAM:
<i>And so my brother crammed</i>
<i>three months of partying</i>

19:35.175 --> 19:38.643
<i>into one epic night</i>
<i>of awesome.</i>

19:39.278 --> 19:39.911
<i>As for Pops,</i>

19:39.913 --> 19:42.413
<i>he was starting to realize</i>
<i>it wasn't so bad</i>

19:42.415 --> 19:44.649
<i>to give up a piece</i>
<i>of his freedom</i>

19:44.651 --> 19:47.752
<i>for his family's</i>
<i>peace of mind.</i>

19:47.886 --> 19:49.587
Still got it.

19:50.756 --> 19:52.423
...so he's waiting
for the tow truck,

19:52.425 --> 19:55.693
he stays in the car,
rule number three...

19:55.695 --> 20:00.331
<i>Ultimately it wasn't</i>
<i>my mom's elaborate rules</i>
<i>that put her at ease...</i>

20:00.333 --> 20:00.932
And listen to this.

20:00.934 --> 20:05.102
He's over
at Roger McFadden's
studying right now...

20:05.104 --> 20:07.238
<i>It was my</i>
<i>dad's elaborate lies.</i>

20:07.240 --> 20:08.306
He is such a great kid.

20:08.308 --> 20:10.107
<i>Knowing it was their</i>
<i>last night of freedom</i> ,

20:10.109 --> 20:12.977
<i>Barry and Erica made</i>
<i>every moment count...</i>

20:12.979 --> 20:14.045
<i>♪ It's tricky to rock around</i>

20:14.047 --> 20:15.813
ADULT ADAM:
<i>And it was glorious...</i>

20:15.815 --> 20:19.150
<i>Until the cops raided</i>
<i>the place five minutes later.</i>

20:19.152 --> 20:21.052
<i>♪ Tr-tr-tr-tr-tr</i>

20:22.421 --> 20:26.557
There's a new  <i>Knight Rider</i>
<i>on tonight. Mind if I tape it?</i>

20:26.559 --> 20:29.060
No! Um,
as a matter of fact,

20:29.062 --> 20:31.996
why don't you use, uh,
the new voice command?

20:31.998 --> 20:35.633
For real?
Yeah, for real.
Tell it your name.

20:35.635 --> 20:37.568
Hi. I'm Barry Goldberg.

20:37.570 --> 20:39.837
Now, uh, tell it
to do something.

20:39.839 --> 20:42.773
Remote,
turn to  <i>Knight Rider.</i>

20:42.975 --> 20:43.975
(TIRES SCREECH)

20:43.977 --> 20:44.909
Huh. That's pretty cool.

20:44.911 --> 20:47.979
Wait a minute. Did it?
Give it to me a second here.

20:47.981 --> 20:51.549
Uh... Go back
to  <i>T.J. Hooker.</i>

20:51.817 --> 20:53.317
No, wrong way!

20:53.319 --> 20:53.884
<i>T.J. Hooker!</i>

20:53.886 --> 20:56.487
Tell it to go back
to  <i>T.J. Hooker.</i>
<i>No, you tell it.</i>

20:56.489 --> 21:01.058
All right, remote, this
is Murray Goldberg.

21:01.060 --> 21:03.928
Please go back
to  <i>T.J. Hooker.</i>

21:03.930 --> 21:05.563
(CHANNEL CHANGES)
No! Wrong way!

21:05.565 --> 21:08.666
You know  <i>T.J. Hooker,</i>
<i>with William Shatner.</i>

21:08.668 --> 21:11.068
(UNDER BREATH)
And he fell for it again.

21:11.070 --> 21:13.738
<i>Hooker! T.J.!</i>

21:15.741 --> 21:17.608
I want you to get away
from there.

21:17.610 --> 21:19.343
I can't see,
and it's very annoying.

21:19.345 --> 21:21.812
(TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY)
ADAM: Is it annoying?

21:21.814 --> 21:23.714
Give me that.
ADAM: Whoa. (GIGGLES) No.

21:23.716 --> 21:26.884
I want that camera.
I'm gonna take it
and break it!

21:26.886 --> 21:28.753
MRS. GOLDBERG: Barry!
